5|$|Al-Mansuriya, near Kairouan, Tunisia, was {{the capital}} of Fatimid Caliphate during {{the rules of the}} Imams Al-Mansur Billah (r. 946–953) and Al-Mu'izz li-Din <b>Allah</b> (r. 953–975). Built between 946 and 972, it was a {{circular}} walled city holding elaborate palaces surrounded by gardens, artificial pools and water channels.|$|E
